==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nazarene
<hw>Naz`a*rene"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Nazarenus</ets>, Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ Nazareth.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A native or inhabitant of Nazareth; -- a term of contempt applied
to Christ and the early Christians.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>One of a sect of Judaizing
Christians in the first and second centuries, who observed the laws of
Moses, and held to certain heresies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nazarite</ent>⟦br⟧
